    "However, there is still an unexplored potential in explicitly integrating fine-grained RST structures into the summarization process with PEFT methods, since comprehending the coherence of discourse elements could positively impact the quality of generated summaries (Li et al., 2016; Liu and Chen, 2019; Huang and Kurohashi, 2021), particularly in the context of summarizing long documents (Cohan et al., 2018; Xu et al., 2020; Li et al., 2020; Gabriel et al., 2021; Dong et al., 2021; Balachandran et al., 2022; Pu et al., 2023).",
    "A limitation observed with LoRA and other PEFT methods during the fine-tuning phase is that, while their primary function is to act as a low-rank approximation of the weight matrices in LLMs, they do not adequately capture textual context relations (He et al., 2022; Ghazvininejad et al., 2022; Wan et al., 2023; Zhang et al., 2023b).",
